==English==

===Noun===
'''[[ship]] of the [[line]]'''

#{{nautical}} a [[large]] [[square-rigged]] [[warship]] with up to 140 [[gun]]s on at least two [[deck]]s; a [[capital ship]] from the [[age]] of [[sail]]
#{{military}} {{archaic}} a ship of war large enough to have a place in the line of battle; a vessel superior to a frigate; usually, a seventy-four, or three-decker.  (Totten)

===Synonyms===
*(''square-rigged warship''): [[man-of-war]]
*(''vessel superior to frigate''): line of battle ship

